60
00:03:51,259 --> 00:03:55,448
He said that he wanted to quit.
That this guitar thing is getting too difficult

61
00:03:55,449 --> 00:03:56,379
for him.

62
00:03:56,378 --> 00:04:00,058
This is the third type of plateau. it's called
the cliff.

63
00:04:00,058 --> 00:04:03,838
In the beginning. it's fun you're like "yeah
let's do this bring it on"

64
00:04:03,838 --> 00:04:07,248
But after a while, that passion. that desire
fades away.

65
00:04:07,248 --> 00:04:10,948
and I talk about this more in my outlier review.

66
00:04:10,949 --> 00:04:15,049
The cliff is no different than a dead end,
they both lead to failure.

67
00:04:15,049 --> 00:04:20,459
the difference is that The cliff is characterized
by what we call, "beginner's excitement"

68
00:04:20,459 --> 00:04:25,490
Be wary of the fact that whenever you see
a pretty talented person. You're prone to

